                            <comment id="71837" author="bjornharvold" created="Fri, 12 Aug 2011 08:35:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To be more specific. If the @Query(&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
{&apos;foo&apos; : ?0}
&lt;p&gt;&quot;) has a query in it then pageable doesn&apos;t work. If the @Query(fields= {}) only has fields in it, pageable works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="71842" author="olivergierke" created="Sun, 14 Aug 2011 07:19:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will try to reproduce the bug tomorrow but from taking a look at the code I can&apos;t see the special scenario you describe being a cause for the issue. &lt;tt&gt;AbstractMongoQuery.execute(&#8230;)&lt;/tt&gt; creates the &lt;tt&gt;Query&lt;/tt&gt; object first and then hands it into the paged execution which applies pagination no matter what kind of &lt;tt&gt;Query&lt;/tt&gt; object we actually have. Is there maybe a testcase you can provide to get us started?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="71848" author="olivergierke" created="Mon, 15 Aug 2011 11:04:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems the error was caused by some invalid overrides/shadowing in &lt;tt&gt;BasicQuery&lt;/tt&gt;.  Just pushed a fix and deployed a snapshot to the repo. Feel free to give it a try.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
